.TH "ipr_reset_alert" 9 "ipr_reset_alert" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipr_reset_alert \- Alert the adapter of a pending reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ipr_reset_alert
.BI "(struct ipr_cmnd *ipr_cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ipr_cmd" 12
ipr command struct
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function alerts the adapter that it will be reset.
If memory space is not currently enabled, proceed directly
to running BIST on the adapter. The timer must always be started
so we guarantee we do not run BIST from ipr_isr.

Return value:
IPR_RC_JOB_RETURN
